# 16. FRONTEND TECH ARCHITECTURE

## 16.1. Recommended stack

* **React**
* **Next.js**
* TypeScript
* Tailwind or CSS modules for app shell
* Zustand / Redux Toolkit for editor state
* React Aria / Floating UI for popovers
* Yjs or Liveblocks later for realtime collaboration
* tRPC or REST/GraphQL depending backend style

## 16.2. SVG vs Canvas vs hybrid

### Рекомендация: **hybrid with SVG-first editor surface**

Лучший вариант для такого продукта — **SVG + HTML overlay + selective canvas optimization later**.

### Почему не pure Canvas

Canvas хорош для massive rendering, но:

* сложнее делать inline editing;
* сложнее точный selection/accessibility;
* сложнее DOM-based popover anchoring;
* сложнее maintainable UI around node interactions.

### Почему SVG лучше для MVP и reference feel

* ветки удобно рисовать path-кривыми;
* node selection естественно;
* hit testing проще;
* drag handles проще;
* transitions и styling удобнее;
* легче сделать crisp visual quality.

### Hybrid стратегия

* SVG for branches + node shells
* HTML overlay for inline editable text, toolbars, badges, popovers
* optional canvas layer later for huge-map performance

## 16.3. Как отрисовывать ветки

* cubic bezier or smooth spline paths
* direction-aware anchor points
* per-branch color inheritance
* hit area wider than visible stroke

## 16.4. Как делать topic selection

* SVG group per node
* invisible hit area for easier clicking
* selected outline in separate layer

## 16.5. Как делать drag handles

* node body itself draggable
* optional subtle drag hotspot
* relationship creation handle may appear on hover

## 16.6. Как делать inline editing

* HTML contenteditable/input overlay positioned over selected node bbox
* sync text metrics back into layout engine
* autosize height/width with debounce

## 16.7. State management

Разделить состояния на:

* persistent map data
* transient UI state
* viewport state
* history state
* collaboration state later

## 16.8. Keyboard shortcut system

Использовать централизованный shortcut manager:

* aware of mode
* ignores inputs when text editing
* supports remapping later

## 16.9. Popover system

* Floating UI
* collision detection
* flip/shift middleware
* viewport-safe positioning

## 16.10. Autosave model

* local optimistic updates immediately
* debounce server save 500–1200 ms
* hard save on blur / major action / interval
* offline cache in local storage / IndexedDB

## 16.11. Optimistic updates

Все editor actions должны ощущаться мгновенными:

* node create
* text edit
* drag
* style apply
* comment badge increments

## 16.12. Performance strategy for large maps

* memoized node rendering
* subtree re-layout only where possible
* viewport culling for heavy overlays
* requestAnimationFrame for drag
* coarse/fine render modes during pan/zoom
* throttled path recomputation

